Text: socket vs tibco note win comment below Forwarded by Kim KouriETSEnron on AM Meiling Chen AM To Kim KouriET NRON cc Subject socket vs tibco Yesterdays meeting concluded that real time fuel project should use socket to communicate wtih SCADA to be in sync with other real time application in the group Steve Littel sent his VB codes to me and I am working on it I asked Joe Zhou about TW Deal Analysis on Window He said there should be no problem Window should have IE features MeiLing

October PNR BillingTerrys comment below Do we always cover variable operating costs on our park and ride deals Forwarded by Kim KouriETSEnron on AM From Terry Galassini AM To Kim KouriET NRON cc Ben AsanteET nron Subject October PNR Billing Kim You might want to get on the distribution of this report I have wondered and asked the question Do we always cover variable operating costs on our park and ride deals A ride can have a very negative impact on fuel use Doesnt the Deal Analysis cover park ride deals You might want to check into this ThanksTerry Forwarded by Terry GalassiniETSEnron on AM Michael Bodnar PM To Kevin HyattET nron Steven HarrisET NRON Cynthia RiversET NRON Martha CormierET NRON Teresa NRON Beverly MillerET NRON Terry KowalkeET NRON Linda WardET NRON Randy JanzenET NRON Albert HernandezET NRON Darrell SchoolcraftET NRON TK LohmanET NRON Jeffery FawcettET NRON Lorraine LindbergET NRON Lindy DonohoET NRON Christine StokesET NRON Terry GalassiniET NRON Michelle LokayET nron cc Subject October PNR Billing Attached is the detail for Park N Ride billing for October The summary of charges is as follows

Parknride and Deal Profitabilityis it possible to evaluate a parknride in deal profitability If not would this be valuable If it would be MeiLing and I would like to meet with you to understand what we might have to modify

Nov PNR Billing TWsee Terrys note Forwarded by Kim KouriETSEnron on AM From Terry Galassini AM To Kim KouriET NRON cc Ben AsanteET nron Subject Nov PNR Billing TW Kim Heres the November Park and Ride activity with its associated rates and revenues You might find some opportunities here to use the TW Deal Analysis tool Maybe its Morgan or TK Lohmann who could use this tool to set PR rates to ensure we cover the varialble OM costs As you can see theres not much revenue associated with PR during the course of the month so the impact on linepack and fuel use has the potential to exceed the benefits ThanksTerry Forwarded by Terry GalassiniETSEnron on AM Michael Bodnar PM To Kevin HyattET nron Steven HarrisET NRON Cynthia RiversET NRON Christine McEvoyET nron Beverly MillerET NRON Terry KowalkeET NRON Linda WardET NRON Albert HernandezET NRON Darrell SchoolcraftET NRON TK LohmanET NRON Jeffery FawcettET NRON Lorraine LindbergET NRON Lindy DonohoET NRON Christine StokesET NRON Terry GalassiniET NRON Michelle LokayET nron cc Morgan GottsponerET NRON Sue NevilleET NRON Kay ThreetET NRON Reyna CabreraET nron Subject Nov PNR Billing TW Attached is the detail for Park N Ride billing for November The summary of charges is as follows

ParkNRide EconomicsMichelleKimberly I was looking at the economics for ParkNRides on the TW Mainline Leg thought you might be interested in this According to Gary Choquette it costs us in fuel Mscfd for storage of Mscf of gas Assuming a BTU factor of and at a gas cost of per MMBTUfuel costs amount to day Adding OM to this assuming fuel cost the total cost of this storage to us is cents Kim Kouri
